                android:text="1. Prepare the Polenta:

In a medium saucepan, bring water or chicken broth to a boil.

Gradually whisk in the polenta, stirring constantly to prevent lumps.

Reduce the heat to low and simmer the polenta, stirring frequently, until it thickens. This usually takes about 15-20 minutes.

Stir in grated Parmesan cheese and butter. Season with salt to taste. Continue to cook until the polenta is creamy and smooth.

2. Cook the Shrimp:

In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat.

Add minced garlic and red pepper flakes. Sauté for about 1 minute until the garlic is fragrant but not browned.

Add the shrimp to the skillet and cook for 2-3 minutes per side until they start to turn pink.

Pour in the white wine and let it simmer for another 2 minutes.

Add the halved cherry tomatoes to the skillet and cook for an additional 2-3 minutes until the tomatoes soften.

Season the shrimp mixture with salt and black pepper to taste. Stir in fresh chopped parsley.

3. Serve:

Spoon the creamy polenta onto serving plates.

Top the polenta with the Venetian shrimp and tomato mixture.

Garnish with additional parsley if desired.

Serve immediately and enjoy your Venetian Shrimp with Polenta!"
